      "original_url": "https://aircrewremembered.com/wellburn-dennis.html",
      "summary": "Lancaster JB132 of 61 Squadron departed RAF Syerston at 20:08 on 31 August 1943 to bomb Berlin. Returning at 03:26 on 1 September, it collided head-on at 1,500 feet with Lancaster R5698 of 1654 HCU. An explosion and fire occurred in mid-air, killing all 8 crew including Sqn Ldr Dennis Crosby Wellburn DFC, aged 27.",
